WENTZVILLE, Mo. (AP) — A man is hospitalized with what are believed to be non-life-threatening injuries after being shot by police in the eastern Missouri town of Wentzville.The shooting happened Wednesday. Police said a man and woman had given a 53-year-old man a ride in nearby Lincoln County.Something happened during the ride and the man and woman exited the highway and went into a store, where they contacted police.Police say officers tried to talk to the man but he threatened to harm himself. Two officers fired shots and the man was struck in the arm. Police say the man did not fire his weapon, so it wasn’t clear what prompted the officers to shoot.